# Southwest Cilantro Lime Corn Salad

> #side #texmex

![](5DEDC47A-C418-4287-BAEB-2E0AADEFF9AE.jpg)

- Olive Oil | 2 tsp | 

Heat a 12 inch skillet (cast iron works beautifully here) over MED HIGH heat. Add olive oil and heat through.

- Frozen Corn | 4 cups | Thawed
- Pepper | Red Bell, 1/3 - 1/2 cup | Diced
- Jalape√±os | 1 - 2 | Minced
- Onion | Red, 1/2, medium | Finely diced

Add corn, bell pepper, jalapeno, and onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, about 8 minutes, until lightly golden brown.

- Kosher Salt | 1/2 tsp | 
- Black Pepper | 1/4 tsp | 
- Cilantro | 3 tbsp | Minced
- Lime | 1 tbsp | Juiced

Season with salt and pepper and stir in cilantro and lime juice.
